{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868546278,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a037bf8001DZyPDa9maQ35eC","messageID":"msg_d7a036d45001nC0nhJc3qlefjG","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/tests.md","description":"Read AR-013 tests.md template"},"output":"# AR-013 Test Specification\n\n## Test Coverage Requirements\n\n- Redis client initialization tests\n- Store method implementation tests\n- Pipeline operation tests\n- Error handling and translation tests\n- Index management tests\n- Mock-based unit tests\n- Integration tests with Redis server\n\n## Test Cases\n\n(TBD - Test cases to be defined)\n\n## Test Files\n\n(TBD)\n","metadata":{"output":"# AR-013 Test Specification\n\n## Test Coverage Requirements\n\n- Redis client initialization tests\n- Store method implementation tests\n- Pipeline operation tests\n- Error handling and translation tests\n- Index management tests\n- Mock-based unit tests\n- Integration tests with Redis server\n\n## Test Cases\n\n(TBD - Test cases to be defined)\n\n## Test Files\n\n(TBD)\n","exit":0,"description":"Read AR-013 tests.md template","truncated":false},"title":"Read AR-013 tests.md template","time":{"start":1775868546256,"end":1775868546277}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868546284,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a038427001AvYvn1bGCtMxbO","messageID":"msg_d7a036d45001nC0nhJc3qlefjG","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"head -100 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/delta-spec.md","description":"Read first 100 lines of AR-013 delta-spec.md"},"output":"# AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-013  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n\nThe Redis Storage Implementation provides concrete implementations of the Store interface using Redis and Valkey as backends. It handles connection management, command execution, and backend-specific error handling while maintaining compatibility with the abstract Store interface defined in AR-012.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Redis Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Redis-backed Store implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` that satisfies the Store interface.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Ping returns PONG\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis server at `REDIS_ADDR`\n- **AND** a valid `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command\n- **AND** require string response `PONG`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Ping fails on connection error\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable Redis server\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n- **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Redis\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `redis.Nil` error\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Redis\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates input\n- **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n  - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n- **AND** all commands SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n- **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL return `false`\n- **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n\n#### Scenario: Redis UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n","metadata":{"output":"# AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Redis Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-013  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M  \n**Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n\nThe Redis Storage Implementation provides concrete implementations of the Store interface using Redis and Valkey as backends. It handles connection management, command execution, and backend-specific error handling while maintaining compatibility with the abstract Store interface defined in AR-012.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Redis Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Redis-backed Store implementation using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` that satisfies the Store interface.\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Ping returns PONG\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis server at `REDIS_ADDR`\n- **AND** a valid `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command\n- **AND** require string response `PONG`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Redis Ping fails on connection error\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable Redis server\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n- **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Redis\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect `redis.Nil` error\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Redis GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Redis\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates input\n- **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Redis commands\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n  - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n- **AND** all commands SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: Redis StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n- **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL return `false`\n- **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n\n#### Scenario: Redis UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist\n- **AND** a `redisStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n","exit":0,"description":"Read first 100 lines of AR-013 delta-spec.md","truncated":false},"title":"Read first 100 lines of AR-013 delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775868546266,"end":1775868546281}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775868546308,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a038ceb001JCsBpBOsaoYhXc","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a036d45001nC0nhJc3qlefjG","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":16799,"input":4,"output":189,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":846,"read":15760}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775868547666,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a03924f001bmahLCwvGmVHQo","messageID":"msg_d7a038d1a001CQc0FsjCiEcBSl","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868549858,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a039452001N1AI5LnZ2RK15u","messageID":"msg_d7a038d1a001CQc0FsjCiEcBSl","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_functions.bash:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"head -80 /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-013/design.md","description":"Read first 80 lines of AR-013 design.md"},"output":"# AR-013 Design: Redis Storage Implementation\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-013  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium\n\nThe Redis Storage Implementation provides a unified storage abstraction for persisting sandbox session metadata. It implements the `Store` interface with support for both **Redis** and **Valkey** backends, enabling CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times to support garbage collection and idle detection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              pkg/store                                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  ┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │   Store     │◄───┤  redisStore      │    │  valkeyStore            │     │\n│  │  Interface  │    │  (go-redis/v9)   │    │  (valkey-go)            │     │\n│  └──────┬──────┘    └──────────────────┘    └─────────────────────────┘     │\n│         │                                                                    │\n│         └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────►   │\n│                              Storage() Singleton                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Interface-Based Design**: The `Store` interface abstracts backend specifics, enabling seamless provider switching via the `STORE_TYPE` environment variable.\n\n2. **ZSET-Based Indexing**: Redis Sorted Sets (ZSET) provide O(log N) range queries for:\n   - `session:expiry` - Track sandbox expiration times\n   - `session:last_activity` - Track last activity timestamps\n\n3. **Pipeline Operations**: Multi-command pipelines ensure atomic index updates during `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` operations.\n\n4. **Singleton with sync.Once**: Guarantees single initialization across concurrent goroutines, with fatal logging on initialization failure.\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Store Interface\n\nThe `Store` interface defines the contract for all storage implementations:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Redis Implementation\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n    sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Constant | Value | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n","metadata":{"output":"# AR-013 Design: Redis Storage Implementation\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-013  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Medium\n\nThe Redis Storage Implementation provides a unified storage abstraction for persisting sandbox session metadata. It implements the `Store` interface with support for both **Redis** and **Valkey** backends, enabling CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times to support garbage collection and idle detection.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              pkg/store                                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  ┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │   Store     │◄───┤  redisStore      │    │  valkeyStore            │     │\n│  │  Interface  │    │  (go-redis/v9)   │    │  (valkey-go)            │     │\n│  └──────┬──────┘    └──────────────────┘    └─────────────────────────┘     │\n│         │                                                                    │\n│         └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────►   │\n│                              Storage() Singleton                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Interface-Based Design**: The `Store` interface abstracts backend specifics, enabling seamless provider switching via the `STORE_TYPE` environment variable.\n\n2. **ZSET-Based Indexing**: Redis Sorted Sets (ZSET) provide O(log N) range queries for:\n   - `session:expiry` - Track sandbox expiration times\n   - `session:last_activity` - Track last activity timestamps\n\n3. **Pipeline Operations**: Multi-command pipelines ensure atomic index updates during `StoreSandbox` and `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` operations.\n\n4. **Singleton with sync.Once**: Guarantees single initialization across concurrent goroutines, with fatal logging on initialization failure.\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Store Interface\n\nThe `Store` interface defines the contract for all storage implementations:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Redis Implementation\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n    sessionPrefix        string           // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string           // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string           // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Constant | Value | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n","exit":0,"description":"Read first 80 lines of AR-013 design.md","truncated":false},"title":"Read first 80 lines of AR-013 design.md","time":{"start":1775868549839,"end":1775868549855}}}}
