{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868650339,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a03e7fe001Oixtx8ftjAa34y","messageID":"msg_d7a03b3aa001tOKUlAZIFWl3t6","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:17","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/plan.md","content":"# AR-014 Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase Overview\n\n| Phase | Description | Status |\n|-------|-------------|--------|\n| 1 | Valkey Client Setup | pending |\n| 2 | Core Store Methods | pending |\n| 3 | Index Management | pending |\n| 4 | Error Handling | pending |\n| 5 | Unit Tests | pending |\n| 6 | Integration Tests | pending |\n| 7 | Documentation | pending |\n\n## Tasks\n\n(TBD - Tasks to be defined)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- AR-012: 会话存储接口定义 (Store interface must be defined)\n- AR-013: Redis 存储实现 (Reference implementation for patterns)\n\n## Timeline\n\n(TBD)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/plan.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/plan.md","time":{"start":1775868650308,"end":1775868650337}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868650341,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a03fa410011JIj24WzQY8wV0","messageID":"msg_d7a03b3aa001tOKUlAZIFWl3t6","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:18","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/notes.md","content":"# AR-014 Notes\n\n## Valkey 存储实现\n\nProject: agentcube\nModule: pkg/store\nLanguage: Go\nSize: S\n\n## Key Decisions\n\n(TBD - To be recorded during implementation)\n\n## Open Questions\n\n(TBD)\n\n## References\n\n- AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n- AR-013: Redis 存储实现\n- Valkey Go Client: https://github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/notes.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/notes.md","time":{"start":1775868650311,"end":1775868650340}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868650343,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a040763001GF07SRyQS14wc8","messageID":"msg_d7a03b3aa001tOKUlAZIFWl3t6","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tests.md","content":"# AR-014 Test Specification\n\n## Test Coverage Requirements\n\n- Valkey client initialization tests\n- Store method implementation tests\n- Pipeline operation tests\n- Error handling and translation tests\n- Index management tests\n- Mock-based unit tests\n- Integration tests with Valkey server\n\n## Test Cases\n\n(TBD - Test cases to be defined)\n\n## Test Files\n\n(TBD)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tests.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tests.md","time":{"start":1775868650313,"end":1775868650342}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868650345,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a041284001U11H3nkj1YZk5f","messageID":"msg_d7a03b3aa001tOKUlAZIFWl3t6","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:20","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","content":"# AR-014 Design: Valkey Storage Implementation\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-014  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** Small\n\nThe Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete storage backend for persisting sandbox session metadata using Valkey. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this implementation follows similar patterns to AR-013 while utilizing the valkey-go client library.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              pkg/store                                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  ┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │   Store     │◄───┤  redisStore      │    │  valkeyStore            │     │\n│  │  Interface  │    │  (go-redis/v9)   │    │  (valkey-go)            │     │\n│  └──────┬──────┘    └──────────────────┘    └─────────────────────────┘     │\n│         │                                                                    │\n│         └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────►   │\n│                              Storage() Singleton                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Design Decisions\n\n(TBD - To be documented during implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Valkey Implementation\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client      // valkey-go client\n    sessionPrefix        string             // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string             // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string             // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n(TBD)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n(TBD - To be documented during implementation)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/design.md","time":{"start":1775868650316,"end":1775868650344}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868650347,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a043990001uU7BGlCBCF2tfG","messageID":"msg_d7a03b3aa001tOKUlAZIFWl3t6","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:21","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现 (Valkey Storage Implementation) - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-014  \n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** [AR-012: 会话存储接口定义](../AR-012/delta-spec.md)\n\nThe Valkey Storage Implementation provides a concrete implementation of the Store interface using Valkey as the backend. Valkey is a Redis-compatible storage engine, and this AR leverages the `valkey-go` client library to provide CRUD operations on sandbox information with sorted set indexes for expiry and last activity times.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Valkey Store Implementation\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Valkey-backed Store implementation using `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` that satisfies the Store interface.\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Ping returns PONG\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server at `VALKEY_ADDR`\n- **AND** a valid `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `PING` command\n- **AND** require string response `PONG`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Ping fails on connection error\n- **GIVEN** an unreachable Valkey server\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return a non-nil error indicating connection failure\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox\n- **GIVEN** a session exists with key `session:abc123` containing valid JSON\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL issue `GET session:abc123`\n- **AND** return the unmarshaled `*types.SandboxInfo`\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID returns ErrNotFound for missing key\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:abc123` exists in Valkey\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc123\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect nil/empty result\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey GetSandboxBySessionID rejects empty session ID\n- **GIVEN** an empty session ID `\"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT query Valkey\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates input\n- **GIVEN** a nil sandbox pointer\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sandbox is nil\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates SessionID\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `SessionID = \"\"`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating sessionID is empty\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox validates ExpiresAt\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero time)\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error indicating expiresAt is zero\n- **AND** SHALL NOT execute any Valkey commands\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Now().Add(time.Hour)`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n  - `SETNX session:sess-1 {json}`\n  - `ZADD session:expiry {expires_unix} sess-1`\n  - `ZADD session:last_activity {now_unix} sess-1`\n- **AND** all commands SHALL succeed\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey StoreSandbox fails if session already exists\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` already exists\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called with same SessionID\n- **THEN** `SETNX` SHALL indicate key exists\n- **AND** the implementation SHALL return error indicating session already exists\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox requires existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` does NOT exist in Valkey\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound` if key does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSandbox succeeds for existing key\n- **GIVEN** a valid sandbox with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"`\n- **AND** key `session:sess-1` exists in Valkey\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `SET session:sess-1 {json} XX`\n- **AND** update the JSON value\n- **AND** return `nil` error\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session and indexes\n- **GIVEN** a session key `session:sess-1` exists\n- **AND** `session:expiry` has member `sess-1`\n- **AND** `session:last_activity` has member `sess-1`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute in a pipeline:\n  - `DEL session:sess-1`\n  - `ZREM session:expiry sess-1`\n  - `ZREM session:last_activity sess-1`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey DeleteSandboxBySessionID returns error for missing key\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:sess-1` exists\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"sess-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL detect no key was deleted\n- **AND** return `ErrNotFound`\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sessions\n- **GIVEN** `session:expiry` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n- **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry 0 {before} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n- **AND** return results ordered by expiry time (ascending)\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sessions\n- **GIVEN** `session:last_activity` ZSET contains entries with scores (timestamps)\n- **AND** some entries have scores less than or equal to `before` timestamp\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity 0 {before} LIMIT 0 {limit}`\n- **AND** return slice of `*types.SandboxInfo` for each session found\n- **AND** return results ordered by last activity time (ascending)\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey UpdateSessionLastActivity updates ZSET\n- **GIVEN** a session with `SessionID=\"sess-1\"` exists\n- **AND** current time is `now`\n- **AND** a `valkeyStore` instance\n- **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"sess-1\", now)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL execute `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} sess-1`\n- **AND** return `nil` error on success\n\n#### Scenario: Valkey Close releases connections\n- **GIVEN** a `valkeyStore` instance with active connections\n- **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation SHALL close the Valkey client\n- **AND** release all connection resources\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Default |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Storage backend type (valkey) | - |\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Valkey server address | `localhost:6379` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Valkey authentication password | - |\n| `VALKEY_DB` | Valkey database number | `0` |\n| `VALKEY_POOL_SIZE` | Connection pool size | `10` |\n| `VALKEY_MIN_IDLE_CONNS` | Minimum idle connections | `5` |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` - Valkey Go client\n\n---\n\n## Notes\n\n- Valkey is Redis-compatible, so the command patterns mirror AR-013\n- The valkey-go client uses a different API pattern compared to go-redis/v9\n- Pipeline/Multi operations should be implemented using valkey-go's DoMulti\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775868650319,"end":1775868650345}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868650348,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a04fd97001PY601Dx3NS2z6b","messageID":"msg_d7a03b3aa001tOKUlAZIFWl3t6","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:22","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","content":"# AR-014 Tasks\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document tracks the implementation tasks for AR-014: Valkey Storage Implementation.\n\n## Task List\n\n(TBD - Tasks to be defined during implementation)\n\n### Phase 1: Valkey Client Setup\n\n- [ ] Add valkey-go dependency to go.mod\n- [ ] Define valkeyStore struct\n- [ ] Implement NewValkeyStore constructor\n- [ ] Implement client configuration from environment variables\n\n### Phase 2: Core Store Methods\n\n- [ ] Implement Ping method\n- [ ] Implement GetSandboxBySessionID method\n- [ ] Implement StoreSandbox method\n- [ ] Implement UpdateSandbox method\n- [ ] Implement DeleteSandboxBySessionID method\n\n### Phase 3: Index Management\n\n- [ ] Implement ListExpiredSandboxes method\n- [ ] Implement ListInactiveSandboxes method\n- [ ] Implement UpdateSessionLastActivity method\n\n### Phase 4: Error Handling\n\n- [ ] Implement Valkey-specific error translation\n- [ ] Handle connection errors\n- [ ] Handle nil result translation to ErrNotFound\n\n### Phase 5: Unit Tests\n\n- [ ] Write tests for Ping\n- [ ] Write tests for GetSandboxBySessionID\n- [ ] Write tests for StoreSandbox\n- [ ] Write tests for UpdateSandbox\n- [ ] Write tests for DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n- [ ] Write tests for ListExpiredSandboxes\n- [ ] Write tests for ListInactiveSandboxes\n- [ ] Write tests for UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\n### Phase 6: Integration Tests\n\n- [ ] Set up Valkey test container\n- [ ] Write integration tests for all methods\n- [ ] Test pipeline operations\n\n### Phase 7: Documentation\n\n- [ ] Update module README\n- [ ] Add inline code documentation\n- [ ] Update architecture diagrams\n\n## Progress\n\n(TBD)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775868650323,"end":1775868650347}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868651338,"sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","part":{"id":"prt_d7a03bb98001B5rg89eCW6Frut","messageID":"msg_d7a03b3aa001tOKUlAZIFWl3t6","sessionID":"ses_285fd23e2ffewgBJ2AxWJwzI9c","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml","content":"id: AR-014\ntitle: Valkey 存储实现\nmodule: pkg/store\nlanguage: Go\nsize: S\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-014: Valkey 存储实现\n# Module: pkg/store\n# Language: Go\n# Size: S\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: valkey-storage-implementation\n  description: |\n    Implement the Valkey storage backend for the session store interface.\n    This provides a concrete implementation of the Store interface using\n    Valkey as the underlying storage engine, supporting session persistence,\n    expiry tracking, and activity indexing. Valkey is a Redis-compatible\n    storage engine, so this implementation should follow a similar pattern\n    to AR-013 but using the valkey-go client.\n\n# Scope\nscope:\n  in:\n    - Valkey Store implementation of Store interface\n    - Valkey client configuration and connection management\n    - CRUD operations for session data using Valkey commands\n    - Expiry and activity index management with Valkey ZSET\n    - Error handling and Valkey-specific error translation\n    - Pipeline/Multi operations for atomicity\n  out:\n    - Redis implementation (covered in AR-013)\n    - Migration logic from other storage backends\n    - Caching layer optimizations\n    - Valkey Cluster-specific features\n\n# Acceptance Criteria\nacceptance:\n  - All Store interface methods implemented for Valkey backend\n  - Valkey connection pooling and lifecycle management\n  - Proper error translation (valkey nil → ErrNotFound)\n  - Atomic pipeline operations for StoreSandbox and DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n  - ZSET index management for expiry and activity tracking\n  - Environment variable configuration support\n  - Unit tests with mocked Valkey client\n  - Integration tests with Valkey test server\n\n# References\nreferences:\n  - AR-012: 会话存储接口定义\n  - AR-013: Redis 存储实现\n\n# Estimation\nestimation:\n  size: S\n  story_points: 3\n  days: 2\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-014/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775868650304,"end":1775868651335}}}}
